lect, ridicule, and intellectual abuse, Kozo-Polyansky's ideas are now endorsed by virtually all biologists. Kozo-Polyansky's seminal work is presented here for the first time in an outstanding annotated translation, updated with commentaries, references, and modern micrographs of symbiotic phenomena.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aSymbiogenesis. 7aSCIENCE / Life Sciences / Evolution.2bisacsh1 aFet, Victor, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFet, Victor, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKhakhina, Liya N., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMargulis, Lynn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMargulis, Lynn, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRaven, Peter H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP eBook Package Archive 1893-1999z978311044221208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHarvard University Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311044220540uhttps://doi.org/10.4159/9780674056589?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780674056589423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780674056589/original  a978-3-11-044220-5  Harvard University Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  a978-3-11-044221-2  HUP eBook Package Archive 1893-1999c1893d1999  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK